<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-375-446  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 375 446.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Communications News  June 1989 v26 n6 p46(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Boost bandwidth: node-protecting DAX innovations take advantage offiber and ISDN readiness. (digital-access cross connect;integrated services digital network)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mora, Randall; Manno, Phil.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Digital-access cross connect (DAX) based on the synchronousoptical network (SONET) takes advantage of fiber optic's largebaseband.andP;  Commonly, DAX systems are point-to-point arrangementsconnected through standard Digital Service Rate 1 (DS1) trunks orfurther multiplexed to DS3.andP;  When using fiber as a medium, ratescan include SONET Rate 1 at 51M-bps and SONET Rate 3 at 155M-bps.andO;Detailed plans for setting up a three-cornered transcontinentalvoice-data-video network are given.andP;  The solution described iscost-competitive with T1 DAX systems and moves networks closer toimplementation of ISDN.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Cost of CommunicationsTelecommunicationsCommunications ManagementFiber OpticsWide Area NetworksTutorialSynchronousOptical CommunicationsNetworksT1 CommunicationsSONET (Computer Network Protocol)BroadbandDigital Communications.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Network diagrams. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>